  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promotion of freedom of expression, online and off-line, including celebration of World Press Freedom Day (WPFD) and addressing emerging challenges to freedom of expression and related human rights in the digital age</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This activity directly contributes to Program V / MLA 1 on advancing freedom of expression online as offline and promoting Internet Universality. UNESCO plays and should reinforce its leading role in promoting freedom of expression, and to foster policy improvement at global, regional and national levels. This activity will include tackling hate speech with a right-based approach, and advancing freedom of expression in times of elections. The celebration of WPFD (3 May) will constitute a cornerstone of UNESCO&apos;s awareness-raising efforts on press freedom and the safety of journalists, along with the production and dissemination of the flagship publications &quot;World Trends in Freedom of Expression and Media Development&quot;.</narrative>
  </description>
